This paper deals with a priority queueing system in a communication network, which is a typical topic in the field of computer networks and communication systems (cs.NI). The concept of Peak Age of Information (PAoI) is related to information theory (cs.IT) and the study of information freshness in communication systems. The paper also involves the analysis of service disciplines and buffer sizes, which are common topics in control systems (cs.SY) and performance analysis (cs.PF). Finally, the paper uses mathematical models and analysis to derive exact and approximate results, which is a typical approach in the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
